CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 3, 1962, pg. 10, reads: "Renewal Council - Among those present at the initiation of new members at Sportsmen's Post 913, Sunday, at the post home in Brushton, were (left to right): James Cunningham, associate director, ACTION-Housing; Mrs. Chestnut, Mrs. Jones, Mrs. Roberts, P. C.; Thomas Jefferson, Joseph Stribling, post commander; Mrs. Boulden, Kernon Stimson, executive director, Homewood-Brushton Renewal; Mrs. Wilbur Nelson, city services, Homewood; Harold McClain, P. C.; Joseph Watson, general chairman, and Robert Gibbs."
TitMainTitle: American Legion Sportsmen's Post 913 members James Cunningham, Mrs. Chestnut, Mrs. Jones, Mrs. Roberts, Thomas Jefferson, Joseph Stribling, Mrs. Boulden, Kernon Stimson, Mrs. Wilbur Nelson, Harold McClain, Joseph Watson, and Robert Gibbs seated around table in post 913 home, with jukebox in background and streamers overhead, Brushton
